    <h1>Elevon Atoms</h1>
    <p>Elevon utilizes the term <em>Atoms</em> to refer to CSS variables, which are also known as custom properties. The utilization of these variables is an essential aspect of Elevon's design system, as they serve as the fundamental guidelines for creating a consistent style.</p>
    <p>Adopting the practice of utilizing variables in design reduces redundancy, enhances consistency, and simplifies the maintenance of the codebase. Moreover, developers can modify these variables to meet their specific needs, facilitating the customization of Elevon's design.</p>
    <p>Elevon encourages the modification of their Atoms by developers. However, it is important to refrain from splitting them.</p>    
